Thanks — addressed all three:

1. Multi-parent CRITICAL: implementer now passes list(proposal.parent_commits) straight into GitRepo.commit_tree (which takes Iterable[str]), so single-parent and merge-parent proposals both round-trip correctly. The scripted planner in 8b only emits single-parent proposals, but the implementer itself is not limited. Clarifying note added so the scripted/planner vs arbitrary/implementer asymmetry is intentional.

2. Stale 'planner and implementer' phrasing fixed — the harness passes --base-commit-sha only to the planner; the implementer reads parents from the proposal.

3. E2E assertions extended: trial.parent_commits == [base_sha], and repo.commit_parents(trial_commit_sha) == list(trial.parent_commits).

Please review at /Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-8b-service-extraction.md.
